Frank TESCIONA, Appellant, v. James A. JOHNSTON, Warden, U. S. Penitentiary, Alcatraz, Cal., Appellee. No. 8101. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. March 27, 1936. Frank Tesciona, in pro. per. H. H. McPike, U. S. Atty., and A. J. Zirpoli, Asst. U. S. Atty., both of San Francisco, Cal., for appellee.

Before WILBUR, MATHEWS, and IIANEY, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Upon consideration oL the record and brief filed, and by direction of the court, ordered, order of District Court affirmed, that a decree be filed and entered accordingly; mandate to issue in thirty days.
